=== Cardioid as pedal curve of a circle ===

The Cremona generation of a cardioid should not be confused with the following generation:

Let be formula_78 a circle and formula_47 a point on the perimeter of this circle. The following is true:
: The foots of perpendiculars from point formula_47 on the tangents of circle formula_78 are points of a cardioid.

Hence a cardioid is a special pedal curve of a circle.

==== Proof ====
In a Cartesian coordinate system circle formula_78 may have midpoint formula_83 and radius formula_84. The tangent at circle point formula_85 has the equation
formula_86
The foot of the perpendicular from point formula_47 on the tangent is point formula_88 with the still unknown distance formula_89 to the origin formula_47. Inserting the point into the equation of the tangent yields
formula_91
which is the polar equation of a cardioid.

&quot;Remark:&quot; If point formula_47 is not on the perimeter of the circle formula_78, one gets a limaçon of Pascal.

